attribs.name: marquee
attribs.current:
The Inconnu are an ancient and secretive sect of vampires, about whom virtually nothing is known.
The only visible facet of the sect seems to be the Monitors, who watch vampiric events while avoiding direct interference.

attribs.name: bp_slaketext
attribs.current:
Animals & bagged blood slake full Hunger.
Humans slake full Hunger.
Must kill to reduce Hunger below 1.

attribs.name: bane_text
attribs.current: Your Caitiff Blood is too dilute to carry the legacy of an Antediluvian in the form of a Clan Bane. Nevertheless, your clanless nature ensures other Kindred view you as an outsider:  You begin with the Suspect (â€¢) Flaw, and cannot purchase positive Status during character creation.  Moreover, you suffer a dice penalty on Social tests against fellow Kindred who know you are Caitiff equal to one-half your Bane Severity (1), rounded down to a minimum of one.

attribs.name: mortal_history
attribs.current: An impulse Embrace, Ava had always had the vague understanding that something fundamental separated her from other Malkavians, and even other Kindred.  This only compounded her growing resentment, and after only five years under her Sire's wing refused to accept any more of it, leaving the city and traveling westward as far as she could go.  After capture by the Second Inquisition and a brief period of unpleasantness, Ava was assigned to return to Toronto and spy on her Sire.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LON8Va8Z-lgzThxa-kA_advantage_details
attribs.current: The Baroness values your coterie quite highly, but her support is unreliable: The duties of her office demand much of her time, not to mention how difficult it can be to contact her given her frequent relocations and security precautions.

attribs.name: repeating_negadvantage_-LON8ZD9mjSyLC2ZstQp_negadvantage_details
attribs.current: Frederik Scheer, elder of Clan Tremere and Camarilla seneschal of Toronto, has not ceded any part of his city to the Anarchs.  The erosion of Camarilla power has only intensified his fervor: Toronto will remain the Camarilla stronghold it always has been, whatever it takes.  Unfortunately for you, his attentions are firmly fixed on your coterie --- not only are you the baroness' most prized with two of her childer among its members, but your recent activities have proven to be a thorn in Scheer's side one too many times.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LOZywdCG8No-wJtucFe_advantage_details
attribs.current: You can feed from cold blood, rancid blood, and fractionated plasma. None of these provide Resonances. Ventrue may not take this Merit.

attribs.name: domain_haven
attribs.current: A small but classy apartment in Uptown Toronto in a place that values its resident's privacy.  She doesn't like it when other people are over, but will share her home if a friend happens to be in a pinch.

attribs.name: domain_hunt
attribs.current: Johannes Napier generally supplies the bagged blood Ava insists on feeding on, though she's unafraid to seek out alternate (bagged) sources if the need requires it.  She's aware of the movements of several blood banks, legitimate and illegal, she could potentially draw upon.

attribs.name: assets_carried
attribs.current:

Cell phone with data plan

attribs.name: assets_vehicles
attribs.current: Generally relies on public transportation, but if need be can borrow her sympathetic neighbor's car with the right excuse.  Try not to get blood on it.

attribs.name: assets_stashed
attribs.current: Surveillance equipment of some kind, maybe?  Obviously goes to some lengths to keep people from finding this.

attribs.name: ambition
attribs.current:
Survive the Second Inquisition's machinations.  Find a way to betray my hated Sire without being caught and without too many other people getting hurt.  Protect the Coterie through any means necessary.

HOW TO KILL MY VAMPIRE MOM:
>Accumulate Resources
>Identify projects and weak points
>Wait for a moment of weakness; turn relevant information over to the SI

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LON8LMhKuZM6rP1gTYd_advantage_details
attribs.current:
The coterie's shared domain spans four blocks.  Three are in the University of Toronto District, including the Centre for Cellular & Biomolecular Research, the Pharmacy Building, and the Mining Building (your haven).  The fourth is in the Yonge & College Hospital District, and includes Princess Margaret Hospital. 
All four blocks are within the traditional Camarilla domains of Clan Tremere, including the personal domain of Seneschal Scheer.
HUNTING DIFFICULTY: 5

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LON8Nu9ZZyv01nQ4Dxy_advantage_details
attribs.current:
You have minimal connections with and influence over the mortal occupants of your domain.  You have managed to maintain a (relatively) secure haven in the lower basement of the Granite Base Mining Building, and keep students working on the floors above out... but that's about it.

+1 bonus to any rolls relating to interaction with kine in your domain.

attribs.name: repeating_advantage_-LON8PtZ01Qg89BO6UiI_advantage_details
attribs.current:
On one hand, you're one of the younger Anarch coteries in Toronto.  On the other hand, the Baroness has made no secret of the esteem in which she holds you (two members being her childer certainly helps).

It's a precarious place to be in, especially among Anarchs:  The Baroness is popular, so her favour counts for a lot.  But Anarchs have never been ones to adopt Camarilla-style status based on legacy, so improving your lot in Toronto is going to require action.
